summary: Honestly, the more of Michael Sheen's filmography you've watched the better his performance as Aziraphale seems. It's so...
body: Honestly, the more of Michael Sheen’s filmography you’ve watched the better his performance as Aziraphale seems. It’s so different from everything else he’s done and so completely authentic. This is a man who 100% inhabits his roles to the point that I just want to give him a hug every time he looks at Crowley with that pained, if loving you is wrong I don’t want to be right expression.

summary: So I watched “Good Omens” and I am in love with all of the clever little things in the show; such as cleverly planned music with...
body: So I watched “Good Omens” and I am in love with all of the clever little things in the show; such as cleverly planned music with specific lines that relate to the scene at hand and things as small as the book that the American Air Base guard was reading being “American Gods” by Neil Gaiman himself or even the uh “switch” scene (I won’t go into detail in case you haven’t seen it) that had small little acty things that were so cleverly put that you could nearly miss it if you weren’t focusing on it. I love so much about the show it’s so wild.
